metadata.name: Honeycomb Island #1
metadata.description:
So we're back. Hexagons, am I right?

With 'One More Turn IV' we once again find ourselves studying remote islands of unusual geography. Instead of claiming individual tiles on a larger landmass, this time around we each get our own island to assemble ourselves!

Here's how it all works:
- Islands are formed of seven tiles in a honeycomb pattern.
- Tiles have 45 potential layer states - a mix of natural and man-made features painted in meticulous detail.
- Each layer state has a roughly 2% chance of appearing per tile.
- There is also a small chance of bees.

All artwork is 3840x3328 pixel resolution, and 6000x5200 'originals' are available to edition owners on request.
